The paper deals with a problem in submodular optimization, specifically the matroid secretary problem with shortlists. This problem is a classic one in the field of online algorithms and has connections to various areas such as game theory, machine learning, and information theory. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.GT (computational game theory), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.IT (information theory), and cs.AI (artificial intelligence).
